        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-05-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-05-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="176" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d176">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.032/5–948: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-05-09">May 9,
                            1948</date>.<lb/>[Received May 9—2:48 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>834. Brief inaugural ceremony of new Legislative Yuan held May 8 without
                    incident. Session boycotted by minor parties in protest against Kmt decision to
                    recognize all candidates receiving pluralities as legislators, which would
                    reduce minor parties to 22 members instead of 155 originally promised.
                    Negotiations to find a solution to impasse are continuing.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
